<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="136" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,548,1725]" pageId="9" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,277,548,573]" pageId="9" pageNumber="136">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
One of the two known Madagascan 
<taxonomicName box="[793,906,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[793,906,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="136">Microdon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with bronze coloured abdomen. Distinguishable from 
<taxonomicName box="[404,502,585,608]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsara">
<emphasis box="[404,502,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="136">M. tsara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its largely black tibiae and entirely microtrichose alula.
</paragraph>
